    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><div n="1" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Sub dextram uxoris sculptum <lb n="2"/>nabilium facit quia semper Musis <lb n="3"/>cupida dum vixit fuit </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Viri sub dextram clavem <lb n="2"/>quia sculptam facit <lb n="3"/>tabularium tractavit <lb n="4"/>summa cum fide </ab></div><div n="3" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Hac re coniuncta<supplied reason="lost">e</supplied> <lb n="2"/>sunt manus dex<lb break="no" n="3"/>trae duae uxo<supplied reason="lost">r</supplied> <lb n="4"/>fidelis quia fuit <lb n="5"/>semper viro <lb n="6"/>viro aut&amp;lt;e=I&amp;gt;m con<lb break="no" n="7"/>iuncxs <note>sic</note> cara dum <lb n="8"/>vixit fuit 
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Iambische Senaren. Dargestellt sind zwei sich die Hand gebende Arme, der eine weiblich, der andere männlich. Darunter ein Saiteninstrument [nab(i)lium], ein Schlüssel, eine Papyrusrolle, Tintenfaß und calamus.</p>
            </div>
